commit.message:
Answer CKA_LABEL attribute request with dummy value

A bug in RedHat's patched OpenSSH is preventing empty string, so
providing a one-letter dummy label is the workaround.

Fixes #48
README updates adding config opts
Fix off-by-ones
Remove a TODO already done

Typo in stpm-sign.1 doc

The manpage for stpm-sign references using `stpm-keysign` instead of `stpm-keygen` to generate keys.
Style fixes

Session::GetAttributeValue: respond to requests for CKA_KEY_TYPE

This is required by openssl (via opencryptoki)

Session::GetAttributeValue: respond to requests for CKA_CLASS

This is required by openssl (via opencryptoki)

Rework key enumeration

openssl (via opencryptoki) expects:
  * that valid handles are nonzero
  * to be able to retrieve different handles for the public and private keys within a keypair
  * to be able to enumerate them filtering on the CKA_CLASS of the key

This patch handles these issues by statically assigning the handles 1 and 2 to the public and private keys, respectively.

Prevent segfault when C_GetSlotList is invoked with NULL pSlotList

This happens when openssl (via opencryptoki) tries to enumerate slots, and is apparently valid behavior

Fix RSA_set0_key() usage to make verify work with OpenSSL 1.1

Fixes #43
